<header>
<div id="instruction">
	Choose the pieces of advice that you think you should follow in answering IELTS Writing Task 1.
</div>
</header>
	
<section id="body">
  <img class="rightFloat" src="../media/gt_set9.1_07.jpg" mode="1" id="1001"/>
  
<div id="targetspotting">
  <list class="advice">	
  <li><a id="t1">Brainstorm for ideas first.</a></li>
  <li><a id="t2">Close the letter appropriately.</a></li>
  <li><a id="t3">Copy the Writing Task and use it as your opening sentence.</a></li>
  <li><a id="t4">Cover all the points in the Writing Task.</a></li>
  <li><a id="t5">Decide if you have to write a formal or informal letter.</a></li>
  <li><a id="t6">Decide what the purpose of the letter is.</a></li>
  <li><a id="t7">Divide your letter into paragraphs.</a></li>
  <li><a id="t8">Follow the instructions.</a></li>
  <li><a id="t9">Include all the ideas you brainstormed.</a></li>
  <li><a id="t10">Include irrelevant information.</a></li>
  <li><a id="t11">Leave out any of the points mentioned in the task.</a></li>
  <li><a id="t12">Leave some time at the end to check your letter for mistakes.</a></li>
  <li><a id="t13">Make a quick plan for your letter.</a></li>
  <li><a id="t14">Open the letter appropriately.</a></li>
  <li><a id="t15">Read the Writing Task carefully.</a></li>
  <li><a id="t16">Spend more than 20 minutes on Writing Task 1.</a></li>
  <li><a id="t17">Start writing your letter immediately.</a></li>
  <li><a id="t18">Think about who you have to write to.</a></li>
  <li><a id="t19">Write a prepared answer.</a></li>
  <li><a id="t20">Write fewer than 150 words.</a></li>
  <li><a id="t21">Write one paragraph.</a></li>
  <li><a id="t22">Write your address.</a></li>
  </list>
